WEBVTT

00:02.969 --> 00:04.970
Eddie: <i>Finding your way in</i>
<i>a new school is always tough,</i>

00:04.972 --> 00:06.839
<i>Especially when you don't</i>
<i>have a crew of your own.</i>

00:06.841 --> 00:08.941
Dude, how great
is sailing?
[ chuckles ]

00:08.943 --> 00:11.610
Yo, I saw puffy wearing
boat shoes the other day.

00:11.612 --> 00:12.945
He looked tight.

00:12.947 --> 00:16.348
Boat shoes are functional
footwear with a purpose.

00:16.350 --> 00:17.716
Obviously,
you've never

00:17.718 --> 00:19.618
Tried to raise the jib
on wet teak.

00:19.620 --> 00:21.320
[ scoffs ]
[ laughs ]

00:21.322 --> 00:23.022
<i>Culturally, we didn't</i>
<i>have anything in common,</i>

00:23.024 --> 00:24.490
<i>Which is why</i>
<i>it meant so much</i>

00:24.492 --> 00:27.393
<i>When I finally found someone</i>
<i>I could identify with.</i>

00:27.395 --> 00:28.627
[ ding! ]

00:28.629 --> 00:31.196
Did I tell you
my dad knows l.L. Bean?

00:31.198 --> 00:32.831
Leroy leroy bean.

00:32.833 --> 00:34.500
Troy:
I love l.L. Bean.

00:34.502 --> 00:36.535
-- Captions by vitac --

00:36.537 --> 00:37.703
♪ fresh off the boat

00:37.705 --> 00:39.571
♪ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ♪

00:39.573 --> 00:41.707
♪ if you don't know, homey,
now you know ♪

00:41.709 --> 00:43.008
♪ fresh off the boat

00:43.010 --> 00:45.677
♪ homey, you don't know
where I come from ♪

00:45.679 --> 00:46.845
♪ but I know where I'm goin'

00:46.847 --> 00:49.915
♪ I'm fresh off the boat

00:50.650 --> 00:52.351
<i>But I'm getting ahead</i>
<i>of myself.</i>

00:52.353 --> 00:53.619
<i>Let's roll this story back.</i>

00:54.854 --> 00:55.687
Mom, wake up!

00:55.689 --> 00:57.489
Aah!
Who died? Who died?

00:57.491 --> 00:58.424
What? No.
Okay...

00:58.426 --> 01:00.492
I made you
breakfast in bed.

01:02.562 --> 01:03.595
What do you want?

01:03.597 --> 01:05.731
Okay, just hear me out.

01:05.733 --> 01:07.566
There's a beastie boys concert
this weekend, and I w--

01:07.568 --> 01:08.567
No.

01:08.569 --> 01:10.669
I am not letting you
go to a rap concert.

01:10.671 --> 01:12.071
Louis: What's wrong
with a rap concert?

01:12.073 --> 01:14.106
It's the music
of the time.
See?

01:14.108 --> 01:15.674
See? Dad gets it!

01:15.676 --> 01:18.043
Okay, louis, I know
you like to be good cop,

01:18.045 --> 01:20.245
But somebody has to
wield the hammer in this family.

01:20.247 --> 01:22.581
No, they don't.
We could both be good cops.

01:22.583 --> 01:24.450
Like that movie
"good cops."

01:25.418 --> 01:27.586
There's
no such movie.

01:27.588 --> 01:29.955
Yes, mom,
they're rappers,

01:29.957 --> 01:32.291
But they're
<i>white</i> rappers.

01:32.293 --> 01:33.392
White!

01:33.394 --> 01:35.027
Eddie, we have
been through this before,

01:35.029 --> 01:37.129
And the answer
is always the same.

01:37.131 --> 01:40.032
But they're
sort of asian.
No!

01:41.101 --> 01:42.868
But he's a doctor.
No!

01:44.037 --> 01:45.938
You're always talking
about the year of the dog.

01:45.940 --> 01:47.139
That's a stretch.

01:47.141 --> 01:48.107
No!

01:48.109 --> 01:50.742
Eddie, I just
don't understand you --

01:50.744 --> 01:52.311
The music you listen to,

01:52.313 --> 01:54.313
The way you talk,
your clothes.

01:54.315 --> 01:57.316
[ sighs ] why can't you support
something that I like for once?

01:57.318 --> 01:59.585
Well, why can't you be
a good chinese boy

01:59.587 --> 02:01.320
Like evan and emery?

02:01.322 --> 02:03.722
They both study hard,
play violin,

02:03.724 --> 02:05.424
Wear button-up shirts
properly,

02:05.426 --> 02:07.259
Not like you,
buttoning the top button

02:07.261 --> 02:09.394
And letting the rest
flap out like a cape.

02:09.396 --> 02:11.063
That's called
being a "g," mom!

02:11.065 --> 02:12.831
Why do you
want to be a letter

02:12.833 --> 02:15.234
That's only worth
two points in scrabble?!

02:17.570 --> 02:19.004
"q" is better!

02:20.240 --> 02:23.075
I'm sure you all know
why I gather you here.

02:23.077 --> 02:24.343
Mitch has decided

02:24.345 --> 02:27.246
To take a lateral position
at the golden saddle.

02:27.248 --> 02:29.581
As far as I'm concerned,
he no longer exists.

02:29.583 --> 02:31.783
Has anyone seen
my astronaut pen?

02:31.785 --> 02:32.818
Nancy?

02:32.820 --> 02:34.920
I never
should have slept with you.

02:34.922 --> 02:38.624
Okay, well, if anyone
sees my pen in nancy's purse,

02:38.626 --> 02:39.892
Let me know.

02:40.793 --> 02:41.827
I...

02:41.829 --> 02:42.861
I'm sorry.
I -- should I --

02:42.863 --> 02:44.296
D-don't worry
about it, mitch.

02:44.298 --> 02:45.364
Despite your betrayal,

02:45.366 --> 02:46.798
You were here
when I opened this place,

02:46.800 --> 02:48.500
And I'll never forget that.

02:49.469 --> 02:50.502
Thanks.

02:52.105 --> 02:53.772
It's time to forget
about mitch.

02:53.774 --> 02:56.141
I'm going to start setting up
interviews for a new host.

02:56.143 --> 02:58.510
Oh! I-I-I'd
be interested in the job.

02:59.479 --> 03:00.546
Come on.

03:00.548 --> 03:01.680
[ chuckles ]

03:01.682 --> 03:02.781
[ school bell rings ]

03:02.783 --> 03:05.117
Well, eddie,
I'm sure you're wondering

03:05.119 --> 03:06.485
Why you're
in here today.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.487
If this is about
the clay sculpture I made --

03:08.489 --> 03:10.522
No, mrs. Uveda
has an active imagination.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.224
That's why she's
the art teacher.

03:12.226 --> 03:13.492
I've chosen you

03:13.494 --> 03:16.128
To be a "first day friend"
for a new student --

03:16.130 --> 03:19.031
Show them around the school,
teach them the ropes.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.400
But I've only been here
for a few months.

03:21.402 --> 03:22.834
More than enough time.

03:22.836 --> 03:24.803
Plus, I think you
and the new student, phillip,

03:24.805 --> 03:26.405
Might have
some things in common.

03:26.407 --> 03:27.339
Like what?

03:27.341 --> 03:28.707
Let's just say

03:28.709 --> 03:31.543
I feel like you have mutual
interests and experiences.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.212
He's chinese, isn't he?

03:33.214 --> 03:34.046
What?

03:34.048 --> 03:35.080
No.

03:35.082 --> 03:36.348
Is he?

03:36.350 --> 03:39.418
[ chuckling ]
gosh, I'm not sure.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.353
Let's just --
let's...

03:41.355 --> 03:42.354
[ intercom beeps ]

03:42.356 --> 03:43.355
Shauna?

03:43.357 --> 03:44.756
Could you
send in phillip?

03:44.758 --> 03:47.693
Shauna: Sure. Which one is he?
There's a few kids out here.

03:47.695 --> 03:50.062
Uh...

03:50.064 --> 03:51.530
You know...

03:51.532 --> 03:52.698
Phillip!

03:52.700 --> 03:53.899
I'm gonna need
more than that.

03:53.901 --> 03:55.901
W-what does he
look like?

03:55.903 --> 03:58.036
Well...

03:58.038 --> 04:00.906
Phillip is here
to meet eddie huang.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.774
<i>Huang.</i>

04:02.776 --> 04:05.077
Um, principal hunter,
if you could be more specific,

04:05.079 --> 04:07.579
I can get you
what you need.

04:07.581 --> 04:08.747
Here's an idea --

04:08.749 --> 04:09.915
Just say
the name phillip,

04:09.917 --> 04:11.850
And whoever stands up,
send him in.

04:11.852 --> 04:13.318
Because that's
probably phillip.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.757
<i>I couldn't have been happier.</i>

04:18.759 --> 04:21.627
<i>This was the first chinese kid</i>
<i>I'd met since moving from d.C.</i>

04:21.629 --> 04:23.762
<i>Finally, I had a crew.</i>

04:23.764 --> 04:24.896
Yo, what's up, phillip?

04:24.898 --> 04:25.931
I'm eddie.

04:25.933 --> 04:27.366
It's a pleasure
to meet you, eddie.

04:27.368 --> 04:29.501
Come on.
I'll show you around.

04:30.870 --> 04:33.205
Was that phillip?
[ sighs ]

04:33.207 --> 04:36.475
And I have no idea what happens
in this room, either.

04:36.477 --> 04:38.810
The sign on the door
says "library."

04:38.812 --> 04:39.845
Hmm.

04:41.881 --> 04:42.814
[ chuckles ]

04:42.816 --> 04:44.983
Looks like
someone's got a twin.

04:44.985 --> 04:47.386
Looks like somebody's
outnumbered.

04:50.990 --> 04:53.992
Eddie:
Anyways, I've been running
my mouth for this whole time.

04:53.994 --> 04:55.394
Where's your family from?

04:55.396 --> 04:56.461
Hunan?

04:56.463 --> 04:57.396
Jerusalem.

04:57.398 --> 05:01.166
I was adopted by jewish parents.
My last name is goldstein.

05:01.168 --> 05:03.001
Oh, that's cool.

05:03.003 --> 05:04.836
We both eat chinese food
on christmas,

05:04.838 --> 05:07.072
And our parents
are super pushy.

05:10.677 --> 05:12.177
Okay...

05:12.179 --> 05:13.945
What kind of stuff
are you into?

05:13.947 --> 05:15.113
You like
the beastie boys?

05:15.115 --> 05:16.581
I prefer musicals.

05:16.583 --> 05:17.949
Shaq?

05:17.951 --> 05:18.950
Tolstoy.

05:18.952 --> 05:19.785
Bling?

05:19.787 --> 05:20.919
Investments.

05:20.921 --> 05:22.254
"hangin' with mr. Cooper"?

05:22.256 --> 05:24.756
Can't watch tv on fridays
because of shabbat --

05:24.758 --> 05:26.391
Hangin' with god.

05:33.099 --> 05:34.599
Stinky tofu?

05:34.601 --> 05:36.101
Gefilte fish.

05:36.103 --> 05:37.936
Stinky tofu
sounds repulsive.

05:37.938 --> 05:40.439
We don't
like each other, do we?

05:40.441 --> 05:43.008
I find your company
undesirable.

05:44.944 --> 05:47.145
Look who's best friends!

05:47.147 --> 05:50.082
This is gonna get
my ex-wife back for sure.

05:51.117 --> 05:53.218
[ camera shutter clicks ]

06:01.394 --> 06:03.295
<i>After spending a day</i>
<i>showing phillip around,</i>

06:03.297 --> 06:04.830
<i>I figured my time was done</i>
<i>and that would be that,</i>

06:04.832 --> 06:05.997
<i>But I was wrong.</i>

06:05.999 --> 06:07.366
Phillip, go over there
and work with eddie.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.735
I feel like you two will have
great chemistry together.

06:09.737 --> 06:11.169
[ chuckles ]

06:11.171 --> 06:13.772
The pun gun
is set to laughs.

06:16.843 --> 06:20.345
Okay, pair up with the person
next to you for stretches.

06:20.347 --> 06:22.681
Eddie, you pair up
with phillip.

06:22.683 --> 06:24.182
But he's
not even next to me!

06:24.184 --> 06:26.752
Lucky for you, I have
a soft spot for best friends.

06:26.754 --> 06:29.554
Okay, let's
open up those hammies!

06:29.556 --> 06:30.856
<i>I even told principal hunter</i>

06:30.858 --> 06:33.525
<i>About the whole thing</i>
<i>feeling kind of racist.</i>

06:33.527 --> 06:35.894
In response
to complaints of racism,

06:35.896 --> 06:39.331
I now commence
the first meeting of the...

06:39.333 --> 06:40.932
Pacific rim club.

06:40.934 --> 06:43.668
You now have a safe haven

06:43.670 --> 06:46.071
To celebrate
your unique culture.

06:46.073 --> 06:48.407
I'm leaving you a box
of watercolors and parchment

06:48.409 --> 06:50.041
If you choose
to express yourself

06:50.043 --> 06:51.977
Through monumental landscape
painting.

06:56.849 --> 06:59.184
Meat is murder!

06:59.186 --> 07:01.920
Again, I don't know why you
interviewed for this position,

07:01.922 --> 07:03.088
But thank you.

07:03.090 --> 07:04.890
We'll keep your résumé
on file!

07:04.892 --> 07:05.957
[ door opens ]

07:05.959 --> 07:08.126
Beg your pardon, sir.
Name's wyatt.

07:08.128 --> 07:10.762
[ dramatic western music plays ]
I noticed
your "help wanted" sign.

07:10.764 --> 07:12.397
Position still open?

07:12.399 --> 07:14.599
Depends.
You got any experience?

07:14.601 --> 07:15.967
Ah...

07:15.969 --> 07:18.270
Well, startin' in '89,

07:18.272 --> 07:22.107
I spent two years on a
cattle ranch in big sky country,

07:22.109 --> 07:24.743
Gettin' to know every part
of these delicious creatures.

07:24.745 --> 07:27.946
After that, I did a four-year
stint maître d-in' at spay-go.

07:29.248 --> 07:31.950
Ah, who am I kiddin'?

07:31.952 --> 07:33.819
I'm sorry
for wastin' your time, mister.

07:33.821 --> 07:35.220
Uh, wait!

07:36.556 --> 07:39.157
You got the job.
[ chuckles ]

07:39.159 --> 07:40.492
[ chuckles ]

07:40.494 --> 07:42.661
Well, golly.

07:42.663 --> 07:44.396
[ laughing ]
all right.

07:44.398 --> 07:45.564
I...

07:45.566 --> 07:47.199
Don't have a hat.

07:50.770 --> 07:52.838
That's my ride.
Later, nerd.

07:52.840 --> 07:53.939
Who is this?

07:53.941 --> 07:55.340
Oh, he's nobody.
Let's --

07:55.342 --> 07:57.342
Another chinese boy
in school!

07:57.344 --> 07:59.778
Hey, come on!
Let's give you a ride home.

07:59.780 --> 08:02.247
It's quite all right. I'm
just waiting for the late bus.

08:02.249 --> 08:04.049
Nonsense!
Eddie, get in the back.

08:06.152 --> 08:08.620
I appreciate
the ride, mrs. Huang.

08:08.622 --> 08:11.490
Gives me more time
to finish my homework
before music lessons.

08:11.492 --> 08:13.859
Oh, what instrument
do you play?

08:13.861 --> 08:14.793
Cello.

08:14.795 --> 08:16.261
Orchestral?
Solo.

08:16.263 --> 08:17.596
Practice?
Daily.

08:17.598 --> 08:18.630
How much?

08:18.632 --> 08:20.298
Five times perfect
in a row.

08:20.300 --> 08:22.667
If I make a mistake
on the fifth time, I start over.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.204
Yes!

08:28.174 --> 08:29.841
[ sighs ]
arranged the tables, sir.

08:29.843 --> 08:31.776
Ah.
Noticed a couple wobblers
over there,

08:31.778 --> 08:33.311
So I balanced 'em out
with some scrap wood.

08:33.313 --> 08:34.646
And also,
I hope you don't mind,

08:34.648 --> 08:36.214
I edited the sticker
in the window

08:36.216 --> 08:39.518
To make it say "no <i>boots,</i>
<i>no shirt, no service."</i>

08:39.520 --> 08:41.953
Oh, uh, I was looking
at the menus,

08:41.955 --> 08:44.623
And I noticed you moved
the "daily specials" insert?

08:44.625 --> 08:46.324
Yes, sir.
Made it better.

08:46.326 --> 08:47.859
I reckon having the specials
on the left

08:47.861 --> 08:50.061
Makes it the first thing
a customer sees.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.697
Oh.
Little trick I learned
at the cuatro seasons in cabo.

08:52.699 --> 08:53.899
This was
a mess before.

08:53.901 --> 08:56.201
[ laughs ]
it's -- it's great.

08:56.203 --> 08:58.203
Oh, welcome
to cattleman's ranch.

08:58.205 --> 08:59.671
What a beautiful family.

08:59.673 --> 09:02.774
Oh. [ laughs ]
thank you!
[ chuckles ]
this way.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.710
And allow me.

09:06.379 --> 09:07.245
[ gasps ]

09:07.247 --> 09:09.314
Ooh!

09:09.316 --> 09:10.248
Ma'am.

09:10.250 --> 09:11.917
Wow.

09:11.919 --> 09:15.554
And these specials
look so good!

09:15.556 --> 09:16.922
Hmm.

09:21.360 --> 09:23.361
Eddie, will you
sign this petition?

09:23.363 --> 09:25.230
Mr. Hedgehog
is running for mayor.

09:25.232 --> 09:27.566
Evan and I are learning
about the government

09:27.568 --> 09:28.700
In school this week.

09:28.702 --> 09:30.302
Your hedgehog
is stupid.

09:32.104 --> 09:34.673
You made
a powerful enemy today.

09:36.509 --> 09:37.742
Jessica: Eddie!

09:37.744 --> 09:39.377
[ chuckling ]
I thought I heard you come home.

09:39.379 --> 09:40.679
How was
phillip's day today?

09:40.681 --> 09:42.681
Did you give him the snack I
packed for him in your lunch?

09:42.683 --> 09:44.549
I did. He hated it.

09:44.551 --> 09:46.618
[ sighs ] too much ginger --
I knew it.

09:46.620 --> 09:48.053
Do we have to
talk about this right now?

09:48.055 --> 09:49.921
Oh, but there's
so much to talk about.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.089
Mrs. Goldstein called

09:51.091 --> 09:53.458
To thank me for giving phillip
a ride home yesterday.

09:53.460 --> 09:57.395
A chinese boy
with jewish parents...

09:57.397 --> 09:59.264
The world
is an amazing place.

09:59.266 --> 10:00.966
Yeah, mom, everything
about phillip is amazing.

10:00.968 --> 10:02.300
I get it.

10:02.302 --> 10:07.439
Eddie, I am sorry
that I keep talking about him.

10:07.441 --> 10:08.773
I'm just excited

10:08.775 --> 10:11.476
For you to have a good
chinese boy to hang out with.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.478
Now you two
can look out for each other.

10:13.480 --> 10:16.147
♪ yeah

10:16.149 --> 10:17.282
That's true.
Mm-hmm.

10:17.284 --> 10:18.483
It's just a shame

10:18.485 --> 10:20.251
You won't let me go
to the beastie boys concert.

10:20.253 --> 10:22.721
Phillip is a big fan
and needs someone to go with.

10:22.723 --> 10:24.222
Phillip is going?

10:24.991 --> 10:26.491
Oh!

10:26.493 --> 10:28.159
Well, that
changes everything.

10:28.161 --> 10:29.160
You can go.

10:29.162 --> 10:30.495
Thanks, mom!

10:30.497 --> 10:32.464
We can talk about it
with him tonight.

10:32.466 --> 10:33.665
Say what, now?

10:33.667 --> 10:36.001
The goldsteins
invited us over for dinner.

10:36.003 --> 10:38.303
Hospitality isn't dead.

10:38.305 --> 10:40.171
What a family.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.073
What a great family.

10:45.011 --> 10:46.911
I call this one here
the wedding ring.

10:48.347 --> 10:50.348
[ applause ]
man: Oh, yeah!

10:50.350 --> 10:53.518
Always with the lasso.

10:53.520 --> 10:55.086
Mitch:
Hey, hey, louis.

10:55.088 --> 10:56.588
Mitch, what are you
doing here?

10:56.590 --> 10:58.323
Well, I was just out
for an afternoon pedal,

10:58.325 --> 10:59.691
Figured I'd pop in.

10:59.693 --> 11:01.493
[ both chuckle ]
well, you look good.

11:01.495 --> 11:03.928
Thanks. You know,
they're paying me more
at the golden saddle.

11:03.930 --> 11:05.130
Mm.
So, picked up
a ten-speed

11:05.132 --> 11:06.698
And, you know, just been
hitting the open road.

11:06.700 --> 11:07.966
[ laughs ]

11:07.968 --> 11:09.501
You know, I've only
been doing it for two days,

11:09.503 --> 11:11.036
But it has totally
changed my body.

11:11.038 --> 11:11.836
Mm.

11:11.838 --> 11:13.605
Y-you look good, too.

11:13.607 --> 11:14.606
Oh, haircut.
[ laughs ]

11:14.608 --> 11:15.607
Oh, yeah! Okay.

11:15.609 --> 11:17.008
Started going
to a black barbershop.

11:17.010 --> 11:18.443
They have fun there,
let me tell you.

11:18.445 --> 11:21.279
[ laughs ]
like, "oh, what the --"
[ laughs ]

11:21.281 --> 11:22.847
And ta-da!
There we go.

11:22.849 --> 11:24.849
All right.
[ applause ]

11:24.851 --> 11:27.452
Wow. Looks like the
restaurant's been doing
great since I left.

11:27.454 --> 11:29.220
Oh, yeah.
[ laughs ]

11:29.222 --> 11:31.156
Wyatt's been, uh...

11:31.158 --> 11:33.291
Really great.
[ sighs ]

11:33.293 --> 11:34.292
Oh. Oh!
Oh!

11:34.294 --> 11:35.660
I'm so,
so sorry. I...

11:35.662 --> 11:37.295
[ chuckles ]
don't. I-it's okay.

11:37.297 --> 11:39.130
Honestly,
I kind of miss that.

11:39.132 --> 11:41.466
Things have been a little
too perfect around here.

11:41.468 --> 11:43.268
It's almost annoying.

11:45.004 --> 11:46.004
I want to come back!
Come back!

11:46.006 --> 11:47.038
Oh, thank god.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.206
The golden saddle
is so corporate.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.341
They don't treat individuals
like themselves.

11:50.343 --> 11:51.376
It's all about
the bottom line.

11:51.378 --> 11:52.544
They drug test,
don't they?

11:52.546 --> 11:53.712
Yeah.

11:53.714 --> 11:55.180
Put in your two weeks' notice,
I'll fire wyatt.

11:55.182 --> 11:56.214
[ gasps ] really?

11:56.216 --> 11:57.682
[ laughs ]
all right! Great!

11:57.684 --> 12:00.385
[ breathes deeply ]

12:00.387 --> 12:02.520
[ applause ]
wyatt:
Thank you, guys.

12:02.522 --> 12:03.822
Louis: Wyatt.
Yes, sir?

12:03.824 --> 12:05.824
This is, uh,
hard for me to say,

12:05.826 --> 12:07.325
But there's
no way around it.

12:09.328 --> 12:11.429
I love what you bring
to cattleman's ranch.

12:11.431 --> 12:13.565
You're doing a great job.
No notes. [ laughs ]

12:13.567 --> 12:14.733
Thank you, sir.
[ laughing ] okay.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.735
Wow, that means a lot.
Thank you.

12:16.737 --> 12:18.269
All right,
who wants to see the texas skip?

12:18.271 --> 12:19.437
Yeah!
Yeah!
I do!

12:19.439 --> 12:20.772
[ cello playing ]

12:35.087 --> 12:37.188
Hey, how come you don't come by
the restaurant anymore --

12:37.190 --> 12:38.590
I know what you're doing.

12:38.592 --> 12:40.458
I'm not going to
fire wyatt for you.

12:40.460 --> 12:43.128
It's just that you're so
naturally confrontational.

12:43.130 --> 12:45.864
Thank you.
But you always do this.

12:45.866 --> 12:47.632
You always want
to be the good cop,

12:47.634 --> 12:49.400
So you bring me in
to wield the hammer.

12:49.402 --> 12:50.635
Do your own dirty work.

12:50.637 --> 12:53.138
But you're so good
at getting us hotel upgrades.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.472
Shh!

12:54.474 --> 12:56.975
An angel is among us.

13:03.716 --> 13:05.784
Amazing, phillip!
Amazing.

13:05.786 --> 13:07.452
I wanted eddie
to play the cello,

13:07.454 --> 13:10.588
But he wanted to play
"the beatbox" instead.

13:10.590 --> 13:11.823
[ beatboxes ]

13:11.825 --> 13:13.324
Eddie, stop.
Stop spitting into your hands.

13:13.326 --> 13:16.427
Phillip's music
is just so elegant.

13:16.429 --> 13:18.997
I'm surprised
he likes the beastie --

13:18.999 --> 13:20.165
Do I smell food?

13:20.167 --> 13:22.634
Let's eat!

13:22.636 --> 13:25.670
Thanks for turning off the stove
for me, jessica.

13:25.672 --> 13:28.273
These shabbat dinners
are a little tricky for us.

13:28.275 --> 13:29.574
What's shabbat?

13:29.576 --> 13:32.243
Well, shabbat
is the jewish day of rest.

13:32.245 --> 13:34.479
We're prohibited
from doing certain things

13:34.481 --> 13:36.247
From Friday night
to Saturday night --

13:36.249 --> 13:38.750
Turning electrical devices
like the stove on and off,

13:38.752 --> 13:41.085
Uh, handling money,
putting flowers in water.

13:41.087 --> 13:42.654
Mm.
It kind of sounds like

13:42.656 --> 13:44.455
You're gremlins
from the movie "gremlins."

13:44.457 --> 13:45.757
Emery!
[ chuckles ]

13:45.759 --> 13:47.192
What happens
if you get water on you?

13:47.194 --> 13:48.760
Evan!
Believe me,

13:48.762 --> 13:50.461
We'd love to let
some of these rules slide,

13:50.463 --> 13:52.697
But our phillip
is just so strict with us.

13:52.699 --> 13:54.032
Louis: [ chuckles ]
I know the feeling.

13:54.034 --> 13:55.433
We got one
in our house, too.

13:55.435 --> 13:56.434
[ chuckles ]
[ chuckles ]

13:56.436 --> 13:57.769
Mm.

13:57.771 --> 14:00.538
I believe that if you're
gonna do something, do it right.

14:00.540 --> 14:01.606
Yes!

14:01.608 --> 14:02.707
Take it easy, mom.

14:02.709 --> 14:05.677
You are so responsible,
phillip!

14:05.679 --> 14:08.213
This is exactly
why I feel so good

14:08.215 --> 14:10.715
About you two going
to the beastie boys concert

14:10.717 --> 14:11.950
Tomorrow night.

14:16.021 --> 14:17.488
Absolutely,
mrs. Huang.

14:17.490 --> 14:19.157
It's gonna be
a great time!

14:25.297 --> 14:26.931
[ toilet flushes ]

14:28.367 --> 14:31.069
Did you just go to the
bathroom in the dark
because of shabbat?

14:31.071 --> 14:32.704
Yeah.
I ray charles'd it.

14:32.706 --> 14:35.673
Why did you go along
with my lie about the
beastie boys concert?

14:35.675 --> 14:38.009
Because I have
a proposition for you.

14:38.011 --> 14:40.845
I'll go to your
silly rap show tomorrow night

14:40.847 --> 14:44.549
If you bring me to a matinee
performance of "les misérables"

14:44.551 --> 14:46.050
Earlier that day.

14:46.052 --> 14:47.352
Look at this --

14:47.354 --> 14:49.754
A couple of buddies scheming
about who knows what.

14:49.756 --> 14:52.023
I love it.
Don't tell me anything about it.

14:52.025 --> 14:55.226
I'll be in the bathroom.
[ laughs ]

14:55.228 --> 14:56.661
[ door closes ]

14:56.663 --> 14:59.831
I need you
to take me to "les mis"

14:59.833 --> 15:01.566
Because
the rules of shabbat

15:01.568 --> 15:04.035
Forbid my parents
from driving me

15:04.037 --> 15:05.770
And I can't
handle money,

15:05.772 --> 15:09.007
So I can't buy tickets
and a proper souvenir.

15:09.009 --> 15:10.909
And how is
that my problem?

15:10.911 --> 15:12.043
It's not,

15:12.045 --> 15:14.679
But it's your only way
to see the beastie boys.

15:16.582 --> 15:18.783
[ sighs ] fine.
You got yourself a deal.

15:21.353 --> 15:22.620
Sloppy.

15:22.622 --> 15:26.124
For "les mis," you're
gonna want to clean this up.

15:28.761 --> 15:31.763
Okay, so, I have to fire
this cowboy host at work,

15:31.765 --> 15:33.097
And I need your help.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.732
We're gonna do
a little role-play.

15:34.734 --> 15:38.002
I'll be the boss, and you're
the employee I'm firing, okay?

15:39.138 --> 15:40.338
[ sighs ]

15:41.974 --> 15:45.310
Evan, I called you
in here today --

15:45.312 --> 15:46.444
[ sighs ] hold on.

15:46.446 --> 15:49.047
Your face is too cute.
I can't fire that face.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.181
Be more serious.

15:52.151 --> 15:54.152
Well, that's even cuter.
You're excused.

15:54.154 --> 15:55.486
Go. Go, go,
go, go, go.

15:55.488 --> 15:58.623
Emery, though I do
value your work --

15:58.625 --> 15:59.657
My butt fell off.

15:59.659 --> 16:00.992
What?

16:00.994 --> 16:02.160
My butt fell off.

16:02.162 --> 16:03.294
You can't fire me.

16:03.296 --> 16:05.396
This is the only job
I can do without a butt.

16:06.332 --> 16:07.498
I got no butt.

16:07.500 --> 16:08.800
Then I can't fire you.

16:08.802 --> 16:09.667
Yeah.

16:09.669 --> 16:10.735
Oh, gosh.

16:13.072 --> 16:16.107
Mrs. Goldstein and I talked,
and the plan is simple --

16:16.109 --> 16:18.142
After the musical,
you walk to the concert venue.

16:18.144 --> 16:19.978
It's only 3 blocks away.

16:19.980 --> 16:21.579
And make s--
eddie:
I know, I know.

16:21.581 --> 16:23.348
Stick together,
and look out for each other.

16:23.350 --> 16:27.452
Okay, and here is some money
for souvenirs and snacks.

16:27.454 --> 16:28.987
Why are you
giving it to phillip?

16:28.989 --> 16:31.823
Oh, honey,
because I trust him more.

16:32.658 --> 16:34.659
Actually, I can't handle
any money today.

16:34.661 --> 16:36.094
Shabbat.

16:36.096 --> 16:38.262
Eddie, could you grab that
and put it in my pocket?

16:38.264 --> 16:40.932
Careful not to confuse
a pocket for a pleat.

16:40.934 --> 16:42.900
They're pressed,
and they're deep.

16:44.436 --> 16:47.238
[ indistinct conversations ]

16:48.774 --> 16:51.676
God, I love
the mezzanine.

16:52.711 --> 16:56.114
[ opening music plays ]

16:56.116 --> 16:57.815
[ closing music plays ]

16:57.817 --> 17:00.118
Bravo!
[ applause ]

17:00.120 --> 17:01.219
Whoo!

17:01.221 --> 17:03.488
Thank god
it's finally over.

17:03.490 --> 17:05.123
It's intermission.

17:05.125 --> 17:06.791
Man...

17:06.793 --> 17:08.693
[ closing music plays ]

17:08.695 --> 17:10.395
[ applause ]

17:10.397 --> 17:13.231
I feel my life
has peaked too early.

17:16.468 --> 17:17.935
Eddie: [ sighs ]

17:19.304 --> 17:20.505
I'm going
to the bathroom.

17:20.507 --> 17:22.407
When I get back,
I'm reaching in your pocket,

17:22.409 --> 17:23.674
Paying for
your dumb shirt,

17:23.676 --> 17:25.643
And we're going
to the beastie boys.

17:28.313 --> 17:30.515
They're doing
"follies" in the spring?

17:30.517 --> 17:32.550
Um, yes, please.

17:33.852 --> 17:36.087
It is great to be back, boss.
[ chuckles ]

17:36.089 --> 17:37.755
[ chuckles ] it is so great
to have you back, mitch.

17:37.757 --> 17:39.023
[ both chuckle ]

17:39.025 --> 17:41.192
So, the first thing
I need you to do is fire wyatt.

17:41.194 --> 17:43.061
[ chuckles ]
y-you're joking.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.829
I know why you think that --
I <i>am</i> a jokester,

17:44.831 --> 17:47.298
But, no, seriously,
you're gonna have to do it.

17:49.768 --> 17:51.069
Uh...

17:51.071 --> 17:52.937
O-okay.
Okay, yeah, I'll do it.

17:52.939 --> 17:53.905
I mean...

17:55.074 --> 17:56.741
Yeah.
I can't wait to do it.

17:56.743 --> 17:58.009
Great.
[ both chuckle ]

17:58.011 --> 18:00.578
I leave at 5:30,
so do it at 5:35.

18:00.580 --> 18:02.547
I want to be on the highway
when it's happening.

18:02.549 --> 18:03.581
I...

18:05.417 --> 18:07.185
Adios, wyatt.

18:07.187 --> 18:09.020
[ indistinct conversations ]

18:14.026 --> 18:14.959
Phillip?

18:16.195 --> 18:17.795
[ rock music plays ]

18:17.797 --> 18:19.163
Phillip!

18:21.533 --> 18:22.600
Phillip!

18:27.706 --> 18:29.774
How could you
lose phillip?!

18:29.776 --> 18:31.809
You were supposed to
look out for each other!

18:31.811 --> 18:33.478
I don't know, mom!
I'm sorry!

18:33.480 --> 18:35.546
What if somebody
took him?
Don't say that.

18:35.548 --> 18:37.448
Who wouldn't want him?
He's perfect.

18:39.785 --> 18:42.153
Okay, we just have to
tell the goldsteins the truth,

18:42.155 --> 18:44.422
And so you know I'm going to put
most of the blame on you,

18:44.424 --> 18:46.457
Not because I want to,
but for legal purposes.

18:46.459 --> 18:47.859
[ doorbell rings ]

18:49.895 --> 18:50.561
Phillip!

18:50.563 --> 18:52.396
Oh, thank god! [ sighs ]

18:52.398 --> 18:54.332
Hello, mrs. Huang.

18:54.334 --> 18:55.266
Edwyn.

18:55.268 --> 18:56.501
What are you
doing here?!

18:56.503 --> 18:58.669
Oh, well, I got to the front
of the merchandise line,

18:58.671 --> 18:59.804
And you weren't back.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.672
But then I realized
it was nightfall --

19:01.674 --> 19:02.673
Shabbat was over.

19:02.675 --> 19:04.509
I thought that ended
at midnight.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.677
I'm a devout jew,
not cinderella.

19:06.679 --> 19:09.847
So, I bought
this gorgeous shirt myself

19:09.849 --> 19:11.415
And caught the bus home.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.317
You were supposed to go
to the concert with me!

19:13.319 --> 19:14.752
Yeah, I didn't want
to do that.

19:14.754 --> 19:16.354
You just left him?

19:17.189 --> 19:20.458
Phillip, you should be
ashamed of yourself.

19:20.460 --> 19:23.828
Eddie gave up going to
his concert to look for you,

19:23.830 --> 19:26.330
And you broke
your promise to him!

19:26.332 --> 19:28.432
You are very selfish.

19:29.635 --> 19:32.370
You are not
a good chinese boy.

19:32.372 --> 19:33.804
Eddie is.

19:33.806 --> 19:35.806
Nice, mom.

19:35.808 --> 19:37.375
Now drop the mike
and let's go.

19:40.112 --> 19:41.612
Drop the mike?
Who is mike?

19:41.614 --> 19:42.780
Microphone, mom.

19:42.782 --> 19:44.448
It means
you were awesome.

19:46.318 --> 19:49.987
<i>Not gonna lie -- what my mom</i>
<i>did back there surprised me,</i>

19:49.989 --> 19:52.723
<i>But what she did next</i>
<i>surprised me even more.</i>

19:52.725 --> 19:54.559
<i>She took me</i>
<i>to see the beastie boys</i>

19:54.561 --> 19:57.828
<i>The very next night</i>
<i>in tampa.</i>

19:57.830 --> 19:59.997
Whoo!
[ cheers and applause ]

19:59.999 --> 20:02.333
Thank god
that's finally over.

20:02.335 --> 20:04.001
No, that was just
the opening act.

20:04.003 --> 20:06.337
Man...
That was awesome!

20:06.339 --> 20:08.839
<i>So, like I was saying,</i>

20:08.841 --> 20:11.342
<i>Finding your bearings in</i>
<i>a new school is always tough...</i>

20:11.344 --> 20:12.843
Troy: Obviously,
you've never tried

20:12.845 --> 20:14.679
To raise the jib
on wet teak.

20:14.681 --> 20:15.680
[ scoffs ]
[ laughs ]

20:15.682 --> 20:17.248
<i>...Which is why</i>
<i>it means so much</i>

20:17.250 --> 20:20.384
<i>When you finally</i>
<i>find someone you identify with.</i>

20:20.386 --> 20:22.587
Can't keep me down,
goldstein.

20:22.589 --> 20:24.722
You're a philistine,
huang.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.023
<i>But sometimes,</i>

20:26.025 --> 20:27.692
<i>The more meaningful way</i>
<i>to connect with somebody</i>

20:27.694 --> 20:30.228
<i>Isn't the most obvious one.</i>

20:31.863 --> 20:33.764
You saw
the beastie boys, too?

20:33.766 --> 20:36.734
Hell yeah, I did!
It was ill!

20:36.736 --> 20:39.370
I can't believe
they opened with "egg man"!
[ the beastie boys'
"root down" plays ]

20:39.372 --> 20:40.671
I mean, crazy, right?
Oh, my god!

20:40.673 --> 20:41.672
<i>Check us out --</i>

20:41.674 --> 20:43.007
<i>An asian kid</i>
<i>and a black kid</i>

20:43.009 --> 20:45.076
<i>Bonding over music</i>
<i>by white jewish rappers.</i>

20:45.078 --> 20:46.377
<i>America's crazy.</i>

20:46.379 --> 20:48.579
♪ I kick it root down,
I put my root down ♪

20:48.581 --> 20:50.915
♪ I kick it root down,
I put my root down ♪

20:50.917 --> 20:53.117
♪ so, how we gonna kick it?
♪ gonna kick it root down

20:58.457 --> 20:59.924
Mitch: Hi. Welcome
to cattleman's ranch.

20:59.926 --> 21:01.926
May I get you
a table or a booth?

21:01.928 --> 21:04.528
Would you like me to lasso you
a couple seats at the bar?

21:04.530 --> 21:05.463
Ooh!

21:05.465 --> 21:06.497
Lasso, please.

21:08.200 --> 21:09.867
[ chuckles ]

21:09.869 --> 21:11.569
What's wyatt
still doing here?

21:11.571 --> 21:12.803
I couldn't fire him.

21:12.805 --> 21:13.871
Those dimples.

21:13.873 --> 21:14.805
Look, it's okay.

21:14.807 --> 21:16.207
We'll just be co-hosts.

21:16.209 --> 21:18.409
Okay, well, then you two
are splitting a salary.

21:18.411 --> 21:20.244
Wyatt, you're fired!

21:20.246 --> 21:21.579
You're fired, wyatt!
Wyatt!

21:21.581 --> 21:22.647
Wait. Let me
get on the highway.

21:22.649 --> 21:25.016
I don't even
have my keys out yet!
